00:49:01.020 --> 00:49:09.030
So they have found that and there are receptors
in the tendons of the eye, called palisade

00:49:09.030 --> 00:49:15.870
endings, where there are sensory receptors,
for looking at how the eye is positioned in

00:49:15.870 --> 00:49:17.270
the orbit.

00:49:17.270 --> 00:49:22.510
And then of course your whole vestibular system
in the inner ear is devoted to how is your

00:49:22.510 --> 00:49:25.700
head positioned on your neck.

00:49:25.700 --> 00:49:28.410
So, yeah.

00:49:28.410 --> 00:49:31.320
It's very important for you to know where
your eyes are.

00:49:31.320 --> 00:49:39.910
&gt;&gt;male#8: Yeah, I was wondering, I mean, if
