01:04:22.070 --> 01:04:23.410
of its obliqueness.

01:04:23.410 --> 01:04:27.690
And you're taking real advantage of that and
combining that with your stereovision to see

01:04:27.690 --> 01:04:28.690
better.

01:04:28.690 --> 01:04:30.200
That would be my guess as to what's going
on.

01:04:30.200 --> 01:04:33.921
Because, I've noticed that too, not so much
playing tennis, but, if I am looking at a

01:04:33.921 --> 01:04:40.890
tree that's in the dark, but thereís a street
light casting light on the tree at an angle,

01:04:40.890 --> 01:04:43.920
I'll get this incredible sense of depth now
from it.

01:04:43.920 --> 01:04:48.060
Which I think is a combination of the oblique
light coming in setting up certain shades

01:04:48.060 --> 01:04:50.700
and shadows, combines with my stereo.

01:04:50.700 --> 01:04:53.740
And it gives me this wonderful sense of depth,
and maybe, that's what you're getting.

01:04:53.740 --> 01:04:57.790
So take a look and see what the lighting situation
is like.

01:04:57.790 --> 01:05:06.360
&gt;&gt;male#14: I have the tennis thing too.

01:05:06.360 --> 01:05:10.260
Since I don't have stereovision, I only estimate
where the ball is by the angle in which it

01:05:10.260 --> 01:05:11.260
moves.

01:05:11.260 --> 01:05:12.470
So, the light that's coming in and how many
light sources there are plays a big role.

01:05:12.470 --> 01:05:13.470
&gt;&gt; Susan Barry: Right.

01:05:13.470 --> 01:05:14.470
Right.

01:05:14.470 --> 01:05:15.470
Right.

01:05:15.470 --> 01:05:16.470
Because you're using that oblique light.

01:05:16.470 --> 01:05:17.470
Yeah.

01:05:17.470 --> 01:05:18.470
Right.

01:05:18.470 --> 01:05:22.030
And I found when I was stereo blind, the worst
thing was having to climb down outside steps

01:05:22.030 --> 01:05:23.170
at noon.

01:05:23.170 --> 01:05:24.170
You know why?

01:05:24.170 --> 01:05:28.090
Because the light is directly overhead , there
are no shadows.

01:05:28.090 --> 01:05:30.560
And so, everything flattens out.

01:05:30.560 --> 01:05:32.500
Especially if you don't have stereovision.

01:05:32.500 --> 01:05:36.640
So, people have asked me for advice about
when you're stereo blind, I said don't try

01:05:36.640 --> 01:05:38.940
to walk down steps at high noon.

01:05:38.940 --> 01:05:40.100
[ laughter ]

01:05:40.100 --> 01:05:41.260
Yeah.

01:05:41.260 --> 01:05:43.579
Thank you.

